message.content: cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.LG. The paper discusses a machine learning approach to identify homonymous author bibliographies in a curated bibliographic metadata repository, specifically the dblp computer science bibliography. This involves techniques related to natural language processing, information retrieval, and data mining, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
